        "created_at": "2021-09-18T06:07:53.630Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi, I was looking into code of fdb\u2019s simulation related stuff, and I saw that Sim2 actually uses mutex. My understanding is that the whole system is running inside a thread when in simulation model; so why there is a need to use mutex? For example, in sim2_actor.cpp</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">mutex.enter();\ntasks.push(Task(time + seconds, taskID, taskCount++, machine, f));\nmutex.leave();\n</code></pre>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2021-09-18T06:07:53.630Z",
